event: response.reasoning_summary_text.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_0d27bf9f4b2d755a0169e3dd131e2481939dd69d612772f808","output_index":0,"sequence_number":110,"summary_index":0,"text":"**Structuring Fibonacci with Memoization**\n\nI'm outlining the Fibonacci function, starting with how each function call depends on previous ones. When calculating fib(6), it needs fib(5) and fib(4), which in turn depend on smaller values. I plan to show how memoization prevents redundant calculations by storing results, making it an efficient O(n) time and space solution. \n\nI'll structure the response to define the recurrence, compare naive recursion, describe the memoized algorithm, trace fib(6), and summarize the key concepts of dynamic programming. Let's draft this out!"}

